cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper proposes a method to assess the contribution of individual linguistic components in visual dialog models. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on visual dialog models and their performance, which involves computer vision techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an intervention method to analyze the behavior of visual dialog models, which falls under the domain of AI. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper reproduces a state-of-the-art visual dialog model and evaluates its performance, which involves machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the implications of the proposed intervention method for visual dialog systems, which can have an impact on human-computer interaction.
